query.result:
16 Beatrice endured me thus for a short while, 17 and began, beaming at me with a smile 18 such that it would make a man happy in fire:
19 "According to my infallible judgment, 20 how just vengeance was justly 21 punished, has put you in thought;
22 but I will quickly resolve your mind; 23 and you listen, for my words 24 will make you aware of a great truth.

25 In order not to submit to the virtue that wills 26 a bridle for his own good, that man who was not born, 27 damning himself, damned all his progeny;
28 whence the infirm human race lay 29 for many centuries in great error, 30 until it pleased the Word of God to descend
31 where nature, which had distanced itself from its maker, 32 united itself to him in person 33 with the sole act of his eternal love.

